item.title: Look, i need help
item.dc:creator: @Greeny Greeny
item.description:
@Greeny wrote:

[quote=“Leecher Ian, post:3, topic:204990”]elaborate…

btw files arent decompiled// i dont know whats -Xmx500m client

this wasn’t really useful[/quote]

Don’t be an idiot, it was completely useful…

As you can see from your original post, when you try to run it, it says:
Usage: worldid, [live/office/local], [live/rc/wip], [lowmem/highmem], [free/members], [english/germa
n], [game0/game1]

So, let’s think logically, it’s saying “Usage” which means if you want to use it, you need to make some selections from what is after the colon.

So, reading through; worldid, [live/office/local], [live/rc/wip], [lowmem/highmem], [free/members], [english/germa
n], [game0/game1]

Now, worldid is quite obvious, you choose a world number, the rest maybe less obvious to you, but Yz helped you out.

I’m not going to go through each one explaining because I imagine you wont even pay attention. However anyone with half a brain can work out these are arguments required before the client can be executed, they are entered on the command lane when you run your client.
